=======

My Son John chronicles the attempts of two All-American parents to save their
son from the temptations of Communism. Their arrogant and intellectual son has
returned home from a long absence spouting pro-Russian doctrine and deriding the
beliefs of capitalism and the US at every opportunity.
Things get worse when an FBI agent shows up to tell the horrified parents that
their son is an enemy spy.

Kitsch anti-communist propaganda feature from Leo McCarey.

Robert Walker died during filming.
Footage from 'Strangers on a Train' was used in a curious
attempt to complete the story.

